{"programme":{"type":"episode","pid":"p004t4ft","expected_child_count":null,"position":2,"media_type":null,"title":"Episode 2","short_synopsis":"Wendy Robbins tells the story of two women who were raped as a result of the Bosnian war.","medium_synopsis":"Wendy Robbins tells the story of two women who were raped as a result of the Bosnian war.\n\nUsing their legal skills, they took international action against the Serb guards who raped them.","long_synopsis":"One of the many charges faced by Radovan Karadžić at The Hague is that of organising the rape of 20,000 Bosnian Muslim women. \n\nThis programme tells the story of two professional women – a lawyer and a judge – who were kept for months in Omarska camp along with 3,500 mainly Muslim men. \n\nThey were raped and beaten by their Serb guards. \n\nOne of them has now returned to her home town, to find it ethnically cleansed of Muslims like herself. \n\nNot only has she come face to face with her tormentors, she has to endure history being rewritten in front of her. \n\nBoth women used their legal skills and contacts to take international action against their guards.\n\nBut many other women are forced to turn detective, and gather their own evidence to bring their rapists to book.","first_broadcast_date":"2009-11-04T12:32:00Z","display_title":{"title":"Heart And Soul","subtitle":"Bosnia's War Babies, Episode 2"},"ownership":{"service":{"type":"radio","id":"bbc_world_service","key":"worldservice","title":"BBC World Service"}},"parent":{"programme":{"type":"series","pid":"p004t21g","title":"Bosnia's War Babies","short_synopsis":"","position":null,"expected_child_count":2,"first_broadcast_date":"2009-10-28T12:32:00Z","ownership":{"service":{"type":"radio","id":"bbc_world_service","key":"worldservice","title":"BBC World Service"}},"parent":{"programme":{"type":"brand","pid":"p002vsn4","title":"Heart And Soul","short_synopsis":"Personal approaches to religious belief from around the world.","position":null,"expected_child